Git - Guidelines


1.  Initialize Git repository
	> git init

2.  Display current status of project in directory
	$ git status

3.  Add an untracked file to staging area
	$ git add <filename>

4.  Add all files on the current directory to staging area
	$ git add -A .
 	(the dot stands for the current directory)


5.  Unstage a file
	$ git rm --cached <filename>
	
6.  Remove file from staging area
	$ git reset <filename> 

7.  Store/save/commit changes in the staging area to repository
	$ git commit -m "<message>" 

8.  Commit/aAdd files with the same name identification
	$ git add '*.txt'
	(eg. for all files with extension '.txt')

9.  Commit/add all files from the staging area to repository
	$ git commit -m 'Add all the txt files'

10. Display all the changes done
	$ git log

11. Add a remote repository to push files from local repository
    to the GitHub server
	$ git remote add origin <remote repository>
	(eg. git remote add origin https://github.com/try-git/try_git.git)

12. Push/store 'committed' files to remote repository (GitHub server)
	$ git push -u origin master
        (The name of our remote is origin and the default local branch name is master. The -u tells Git to remember the parameters, so that next time we can simply run git push and Git will know what to do.)

13. Check/display changes made to files in GitHub repository
	$ git pull origin master

14. Display the difference from the most recent commit
	$ git diff HEAD
        ('HEAD' is a pointer referring to the differences in commits)

15. Display the changes made to a staged file
	$ git diff --staged

16. Unstage/remove staged files
	$ git reset <directory/filename>

17. Change back files to how they were at the last commit
	$ git checkout -- <filename>

18. Create a Branch (copy) of file from the 'Master' 	
	$ git branch <filename>

19. Display current Branch (copy)
	$ git branch

20. Switch to other Branch
	$ git checkout <branch>

21. Remove files from disk and stage removal of files
	$ git rm <filenames>
	(eg. git rim '*.txt')

22. Commit changes from the Branch
	$ git commit -m "<comments>"

23. Switch back to the 'Master' 
	$ git checkout master

24. Merge changes from Branch to Master
24.1  Switch to Master 
	$ git checkout master
24.2  Merge the Branch with Master
	$ git merge <branchfilename>

25. Delete Branch
	$ git branch -d <branchfilename>

26. Push/save all changes from local repository to remote repository (GitHub)
	$ git push





	
